abstract: Many listeners would never repeat what these podcast hosts say. So why do they desperately want to hear from them?
snippet: Many listeners would never repeat what these podcast hosts say. So why do they desperately want to hear from them?
lead_paragraph: IOWA CITY — The people in the crowd were angry, and “Chapo Trap House” wanted them to stay that way. The five hosts of the popular socialist podcast wanted everyone to know they had all been lied to. About everything.

headline_main: What’s at Stake in the South Carolina Primary
byline_original: By Reid J. Epstein and Adriana Ramić

abstract: He loves South Carolina. He said he will win South Carolina. He spent the days before the primary reminding South Carolina why it should love him back.
snippet: He loves South Carolina. He said he will win South Carolina. He spent the days before the primary reminding South Carolina why it should love him back.
lead_paragraph: HEMINGWAY, S.C. — Joe Biden was moving — two buttons unbuttoned, sunglasses indoors, a God-love-ya in every pot — and the finger-guns would be holstered for no one.

abstract: At a rally in North Charleston, President Trump praised his administration’s response to the coronavirus and assessed the Democratic primary field.
snippet: At a rally in North Charleston, President Trump praised his administration’s response to the coronavirus and assessed the Democratic primary field.
lead_paragraph: President Trump addressed thousands of supporters on Friday night at a “Keep America Great” rally in North Charleston, S.C. It was the night before the state’s Democratic primary and came on a day when the financial markets continued their slide over coronavirus fears. He addressed both the election and the outbreak, along with other issues. Here are excerpts.

abstract: Joe Biden scored a thundering victory Saturday in South Carolina’s Democratic primary on the strength of African American support, a decisive win that could force moderate rivals out of the race and blunt the rise of progressive leader Bernie Sanders.
snippet: Joe Biden scored a thundering victory Saturday in South Carolina’s Democratic primary on the strength of African American support, a decisive win that could force moderate rivals out of the race and blunt the rise of progressive leader Bernie Sand...
lead_paragraph: COLUMBIA, S.C. — Joe Biden scored a thundering victory Saturday in South Carolina’s Democratic primary on the strength of African American support, a decisive win that could force moderate rivals out of the race and blunt the rise of progressive leader Bernie Sanders.
headline_main: Biden Wins South Carolina, Aims for Super Tuesday Momentum
headline_print_headline: Biden Wins South Carolina, Aims for Super Tuesday Momentum

abstract: While members of his administration tried to convey a calm and steady response, President Trump hosted another free-form political rally where he accused his enemies of stoking panic.
snippet: While members of his administration tried to convey a calm and steady response, President Trump hosted another free-form political rally where he accused his enemies of stoking panic.
lead_paragraph: NORTH CHARLESTON, S.C. — Larry Kudlow, the president’s chief economic adviser, stood in the White House briefing room on Friday urging the public — and the plunging financial markets — not to panic over the coronavirus outbreak, while Vice President Mike Pence spread a similar message to officials and residents at an event in Florida.

abstract: Readers share their choice for president and how it has changed in recent weeks.
snippet: Readers share their choice for president and how it has changed in recent weeks.
lead_paragraph: This Tuesday is the big one — Super Tuesday, when 14 states, and American Samoa, will vote in Democratic primaries and caucuses. We recently asked our columnists to make their best cases for the six strongest Democratic candidates.

abstract: Big U.S. banks have been rolling out contingency plans to respond to the global coronavirus outbreak - requiring some staff to work from home, implementing travel restrictions, and talking to regulators about potential stresses.
snippet: Big U.S. banks have been rolling out contingency plans to respond to the global coronavirus outbreak - requiring some staff to work from home, implementing travel restrictions, and talking to regulators about potential stresses.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON/NEW YORK — Big U.S. banks have been rolling out contingency plans to respond to the global coronavirus outbreak - requiring some staff to work from home, implementing travel restrictions, and talking to regulators about potential stresses.
headline_main: Wall Street in Coronavirus Contingency Mode With Staff, Visitors, Regulators
headline_print_headline: Wall Street in Coronavirus Contingency Mode With Staff, Visitors, Regulators

abstract: Michael R. Bloomberg, trying to convey the competence and cool-headedness he says are missing in the White House, will air a new three-minute commercial nationally on Sunday.
snippet: Michael R. Bloomberg, trying to convey the competence and cool-headedness he says are missing in the White House, will air a new three-minute commercial nationally on Sunday.
lead_paragraph: CLARKSVILLE, Tenn. — Hobbled by lackluster debate performances and with time running short, Michael R. Bloomberg is trying to refocus his presidential campaign on his experience dealing with disasters as the mayor of New York, hoping to draw a stark contrast with President Trump’s handling of the coronavirus and the managerial records of some of his Democratic opponents.
